OL,4,CSpeaker took the side of the Labour
OL,5,CParty'
OL,7,F"Once someone becomes The Speaker
OL,8,Fthey're meant to give up their party
OL,9,Faffiliations and become a neutral.
OL,11,F"In this particular case I believe
OL,12,Fthat the speaker took the side of the
OL,13,FLabour Party and it wasn't against the
OL,14,FConservatives it was against the SNP
OL,15,Fbut he took the side of the Labour
