OL,3,CCarlisle MP : 'I believe that The
OL,4,CSpeaker took the side of the Labour
OL,5,CParty'
OL,7,F"I think he came under enormous
OL,8,Fpressure from the Labour Party which
OL,9,Fwas wrong in itself, and shouldn't
OL,10,Fhave happened, but nevertheless the
OL,11,Fspeaker should've kept a central role
OL,12,Fas being neutral.
OL,14,F"The Clerk of the House of Commons
OL,15,Fsaid that he had broken precedent and
OL,16,Fthat he shouldn't had done what he did
OL,17,Fand therefore I felt that on balance,
OL,18,Fthat I think that his role in being
OL,19,Fneutral was compromised.
